Douglas Mark Hughes , 61 , flew through restricted airspace carrying 535 letters to Congress . 
  He landed on the west lawn of the US Capitol . 
  Hughes said he fully expected to be intercepted . 
  He spoke from his home in Ruskin, Florida, where he is under house arrest . 
  He said he wanted to highlight the influence of money in politics . 
  Hughes faces up to four years in prison for violating national airspace . 
 